WORLD champions Wayde van Niekerk and Caster Semenya have been named in the preliminary athletics squad for the IAAF World Championships in London next month.The two Olympic gold medallists topped the list of 22 athletes announced yesterday by Athletics South Africa (ASA), which also included medal hopefuls 100m and 200m sprinter Akani Simbine, javelin thrower Sunette Viljoen and long jump sensation Luvo Manyonga.So far, 20 athletes have qualified for the 2017 World Championships, which get under way on August 4. There are also places in the squad for 100m sprinter Thando Roto, long jumper Ruswahl Samaai and 110m hurdler Antonio Alkana.ASA said that athletes who have not been included in the preliminary team, such as sprinters Henricho Bruintjies and Wenda Nel, will have until the end of the qualifying window of July 23 to achieve the ASA A-standard in their disciplines.The European athletics season is still in full swing and with several South African athletes still participating on the European circuit, some could still force their way into the final squad with excellent performances. The athletics body will be submitting its final team by no later than July 23. This is the time for athletes who are still searching for a qualifier to show their mettle, ASA president Aleck Skhosana said. Work harder and don t give up. There is still a chance for anybody who want to represents the Rainbow Nation at this global premier event. kgomotsos@thenewage.co.za-Kgomotso Sethusha